        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Sending Austin a Spanish passport of 1797.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Washington City</placeName> <date when="1820-03-09">March 9, 1820.</date></p>
<p>Sir,</p>

<p>I inclose, with this, a Spanish Passport of <date n="07-xx-1797">July 1797</date>, in 
compliance with your request of <date when="1820-01-16">Jan. 16.</date></p>

<p>This Passport, (with a number of Papers was received here about
ten days after the <persName>Minister, Don Onis</persName>, had left the City on his way
to <placeName>Europe</placeName>.    I judged it useless to transmit the papers to <placeName>Madrid</placeName>.</p>

<p>If you will give me the Regt &amp; Company in which <persName>Denny Green</persName>
served in the late war, I shall be able to give the information which
you request.</p>

<p><persName>J. Meigs.</persName></p>

<p><persName>Mr M. Austin.</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Mr. Moses Austin</persName> <placeName>Herculaneum Missouri</placeName>.</p>

        </div1>
    </body>
